\f1 <$Scr_Cs::0>
\f2\b Efficiency
\f1\b0 <!$Scr_Cs::0>
\f0 \
\
The current limits of the machine that follow from its token-based foundation, prevents to discharge the human from her responsibility to create an alignment. That does not imply absence of computer assistance in this task. Various technologies exist for this, however, these technologies can never guarantee semantic completeness and correctness of the resulting alignments. \
\
(human efficiency) This can be achieved by a transcription process that can be generic and only requires a specification of how the external semantic meaning relates to what internal semantic meaning. \
